%N A394254 Decimal expansion of the asymptotic mean of the number of common infinitary divisors of two positive integers selected independently at random.
%F A394254 Equals lim_{m->oo} (1/m)^2 * Sum_{i,j=1..m} A037445(gcid(i, j)), where gcid is the greatest common infinitary divisor function.
%F A394254 Equals Product_{p prime, k>=0} (1 + 1/(p^(2^k) + 1)^2).
%e A394254 1.337901945280194785191226984116163054005489381027493...
%o A394254 (PARI) c(m) = prodeulerrat(prod(k = 0, m, 1 + 1/(p^(2^k) + 1)^2));
%o A394254 {my(c1 = 0, c2 = 1, m = 1); while(c2 != c1, c1 = c2; c2 = c(m); m++); c2}
%Y A394254 Cf. A037445.
%Y A394254 Cf. A013661, A065486, A082020, A394253.
%K A394254 nonn,cons
%O A394254 1,2
%A A394254 _Amiram Eldar_, Mar 14 2026
